recalls.Summary: DOPE, INC. IS RECALLING 42,540 COMBINATION CORNER AND BUMPER LAMP ASSEMBLIES OF VARIOUS PART NUMBERS SOLD FOR USE AS AFTERMARKET EQUIPMENT FOR VARIOUS PASSENGER VEHICLES.  THESE HEADLAMPS FAIL TO CONFORM TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF FEDERAL MOTOR VEHICLE SAFETY STANDARD NO. 108, "LAMPS, REFLECTIVE DEVICES, AND ASSOCIATED EQUIPMENT."  THESE LAMPS DO NOT CONTAIN THE REQUIRED AMBER SIDE REFLECTORS.
recalls.Consequence: DECREASED LIGHTING VISIBILITY MAY RESULT IN A VEHICLE CRASH.
recalls.Remedy: DOPE, INC. WILL NOTIFY OWNERS AND OFFER A FULL REFUND FOR THE NONCOMPLIANT COMBINATION LAMPS.  THE SAFETY RECALL BEGAN ON JULY 28, 2009.  OWNERS MAY CONTACT DOPE, INC. AT 1-626-272-1798.
recalls.Notes: THIS RECALL ONLY PERTAINS TO AFTERMARKET REPLACEMENT EQUIPMENT AND HAS NO RELATION TO ANY ORIGINAL EQUIPMENT INSTALLED ON VEHICLES PRODUCED BY THE VEHICLE MANUFACTURER. THE LIST CAN BE FOUND UNDER "DOCUMENT SEARCH" LOCATED AT THE BOTTOM OF YOUR SCREEN. OWNERS MAY ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S VEHICLE SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), OR GO TO HTTP://WWW.SAFERCAR.GOV .

issues.title: Crankshaft Walk
issues.description: The crankshaft develops excessive end play due to thrust bearing wear, causing the crankshaft to move axially. This is caused by aggressive clutch engagement and high power modifications without proper supporting upgrades.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild with upgraded thrust bearings, crankshaft inspection/replacement, and proper clearances
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive clutch drops, regular oil changes, proper break-in procedures, quality clutch installations

issues.title: 5-Speed Transmission Glass Gears
issues.description: The 5-speed transmission gears, particularly 2nd gear, are prone to failure under high stress or power modifications. The gear teeth can chip or break completely.
issues.fix_description: Transmission rebuild with stronger aftermarket gears or complete transmission replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid power launches, proper warm-up, quality transmission fluid, avoid power modifications without transmission upgrades

issues.title: Head Gasket Failure
issues.description: The EJ20 and EJ22 engines are prone to head gasket failure, particularly on the driver's side. This is exacerbated by overheating and aggressive driving.
issues.fix_description: Replace head gaskets, resurface heads, replace head bolts, and address any cooling system issues
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, avoid overheating, use quality coolant, monitor coolant levels

issues.title: Timing Belt Failure
issues.description: These interference engines will suffer severe damage if the timing belt breaks. The belt can fail prematurely due to tensioner issues or contamination.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing belt and tensioner preventively, or complete engine rebuild if failure occurs
issues.prevention: Replace timing belt every 60,000 miles or 5 years, inspect tensioner regularly

issues.title: Turbo Oil Feed Line Failure
issues.description: The banjo bolt oil feed line to the turbocharger can become clogged or leak, leading to turbo failure due to oil starvation.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger and upgrade oil feed lines with larger diameter lines and filter
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil, inspect oil lines regularly, warm up engine before boost

issues.title: Ring Land Failure
issues.description: The thin ring lands on the pistons can crack or break, especially under detonation or high boost conditions. This is common with engine modifications.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild with forged pistons and proper tune
issues.prevention: Proper engine tuning, quality fuel, avoid detonation, gradual power increases

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: The in-tank fuel pump can fail prematurely, especially when fuel levels run low frequently. This can cause fuel starvation under high demand.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump and fuel filter, check fuel pressure regulator
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Clutch Disc Failure
issues.description: The stock clutch is not designed for aggressive use and can wear prematurely or suddenly fail under hard launches or high power applications.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch disc, pressure plate, and release bearing with performance units
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive launches, proper clutch break-in, smooth engagement techniques

issues.title: Intercooler End Tank Failure
issues.description: The plastic end tanks on the top-mount intercooler can crack due to heat cycling and boost pressure, causing boost leaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace intercooler with upgraded unit or repair end tanks
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of intercooler, avoid over-boosting, monitor boost pressure

issues.title: Suspension Strut Top Mount Failure
issues.description: The strut top mounts wear out prematurely due to the aggressive suspension setup and hard driving conditions typical of these vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace strut top mounts and bearings, inspect struts for damage
issues.prevention: Regular suspension inspection, avoid aggressive driving over rough surfaces

issues.title: Boost Control Solenoid Failure
issues.description: The boost control solenoid can stick or fail, causing overboost or underboost conditions that affect performance and can damage the engine.
issues.fix_description: Replace boost control solenoid and inspect vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance of vacuum system, clean solenoid periodically

issues.title: Radiator Failure
issues.description: The plastic radiator tanks can crack due to heat cycling and pressure, leading to coolant loss and potential overheating.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator with upgraded aluminum unit, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, monitor coolant levels, avoid overheating

editorial.tagline: Rally-bred fury wrapped in everyday practicality
editorial.hero_blurb: The original WRX STI transformed the performance landscape by delivering World Rally Championship DNA in an affordable, daily-drivable package. Born from Subaru's motorsport dominance, these early STIs offered supercar-slaying performance with the reliability and practicality of a family sedan.
editorial.essence: The 1994-2000 STI represents pure motorsport engineering distilled into a production car, featuring advanced all-wheel drive, a sophisticated suspension system, and rally-proven durability. It's the thinking enthusiast's performance car, prioritizing substance over style and capability over comfort.
editorial.heritage: Born from Subaru's World Rally Championship success, the STI was developed by Subaru Tecnica International to transfer race-winning technology directly to the road. These early models established the blueprint for high-performance AWD sports sedans that would influence an entire generation of enthusiasts.
editorial.design_philosophy: Subaru prioritized function over flash, creating a purpose-built performance machine that could excel on any surface while maintaining daily usability. The engineering philosophy centered on lightweight efficiency, advanced drivetrain technology, and race-proven components adapted for street use.
editorial.motorsport_history: Direct descendant of Subaru's dominant WRC program, incorporating active center differential technology, rally-tuned suspension geometry, and powertrain components proven in competition. The STI served as both a homologation special and a showcase of Subaru's rallying expertise.
editorial.engine_character: The turbocharged EJ20 delivers explosive mid-range power with characteristic boxer rumble and instantaneous throttle response. Boost builds progressively but hits like a sledgehammer, creating an addictive surge that never gets old while maintaining surprising refinement for daily driving.
editorial.transmission_feel: Short, precise throws with mechanical precision that rewards smooth inputs. The close-ratio gearbox keeps the engine in its sweet spot, with satisfying engagement and a distinctly sporty clutch that communicates every shift. Each gear change feels purposeful and connected.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Planted and confidence-inspiring with razor-sharp turn-in and minimal body roll. The sophisticated AWD system distributes power intelligently while the rally-bred suspension strikes an impressive balance between compliance and control. Grip levels border on the supernatural.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically-assisted precision with excellent on-center feel and progressive weight buildup. Feedback flows naturally through the wheel, communicating road surface and grip levels with clarity. Quick ratio provides eager response without feeling twitchy.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, linear feel with excellent pedal modulation and impressive stopping power. The four-wheel disc setup provides consistent performance with minimal fade, inspiring confidence during spirited driving while remaining progressive enough for daily use.
editorial.sound_signature: Distinctive boxer growl amplified by turbo whoosh and wastegate flutter. The exhaust note is purposeful rather than theatrical, with a characteristic uneven rhythm that's instantly recognizable. Turbo spooling adds an intoxicating mechanical soundtrack.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance purists who appreciate understated capability over flashy aesthetics. Perfect for driving enthusiasts who want track-day performance with rally-proven reliability, those who value substance over status, and anyone seeking an authentic connection between driver and machine.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Luxury seekers expecting premium refinement, those prioritizing fuel economy or low maintenance costs, drivers who prefer effortless cruising over engaging dynamics, or anyone needing cutting-edge technology and creature comforts.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service records, as these engines respond well to care but suffer from neglect. The 1998-2000 Version V and VI models offer the best balance of performance and reliability, while early cars provide purer experiences at lower prices.

expertReviews.title: 2026 Subaru WRX STI Review  The Return of a Legend!
pros: 345 horsepower turbocharged engine with manual transmission
Enhanced all-wheel drive with torque vectoring
Improved interior quality with Recaro seats and digital displays
Competitive pricing starting at $47,000
Better sound insulation while retaining engine character
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Subaru WRX STI successfully evolves the legendary nameplate with significant power increases (345hp), enhanced chassis dynamics, modern technology, and improved interior quality while maintaining its manual transmission and rally heritage. It offers compelling value against European competitors and delivers both track performance and daily usability.

expertReviews.title: The 2026 Subaru WRX STI is Shockingly Bad
pros: Manual six-speed transmission
Rally blue color scheme
cons: Same engine as regular WRX under 300hp
Essentially a trim package not true STI
expertReviews.verdict: Extremely disappointing reveal that feels like Subaru is avoiding making a true high-performance STI. Uses same underpowered engine as base WRX, lacks iconic STI features like big wing, and appears to be mostly cosmetic changes. Reviewer suggests Subaru doesn't understand their own brand or enthusiast expectations.

expertReviews.title: 2026 WRX STI Review  Is This the End of an Era or a New Beginning?
pros: 345hp 2.4L turbocharged flat-4 engine with significant power increase
Refined symmetrical AWD system with active torque vectoring
Modern interior with 11.6-inch touchscreen and premium materials
Customizable drive mode select system
Six-speed manual transmission retained for enthusiasts
Improved chassis stiffness and suspension tuning
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 WRX STI successfully evolves the legendary rally-inspired performance car with more power, refined AWD system, and modern tech while maintaining its core enthusiast appeal. The 345hp turbocharged engine, improved chassis, and updated interior represent a significant step forward without losing the raw, engaging character that made the STI iconic.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Subaru WRX STI Review: Turbo Power, AWD Thrills, and Pricing Revealed!
pros: 345 hp turbocharged FA24 engine with improved responsiveness
Six-speed manual transmission with precise gear throws
Premium interior upgrade with sport bucket seats and 11.6-inch touchscreen
Symmetrical AWD with active torque vectoring
Maintains analog driving experience without electrification
Practical four-door sedan with all-weather capability
cons: No hybrid or electric option available
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Subaru WRX STI marks a triumphant return with a powerful 345hp FA24 engine, refined interior, and preserved analog driving experience. While pricing has increased significantly ($47-52k), it delivers genuine performance sedan capability for enthusiasts who want both weekend thrills and daily practicality. Competes well against Civic Type R and GR Corolla while maintaining its rally heritage and manual transmission focus.

expertReviews.title: The 2025 Subaru WRX tS Is A More Track Capable Rally Car With An STI-Like Price Tag
pros: STI-like suspension and brake upgrades
Lightweight at 3430 lbs (100 lbs lighter than WRX GT)
Manual transmission only
Recaro bucket seats with blue accents
New 12.3-inch digital instrument cluster
19-inch wheels exclusive to tS model
Harman Kardon 11-speaker audio system
cons: No power increase over standard WRX (271 hp)
CVT available on other trims undermines enthusiast appeal
Engine sound not as good as competitors like Hyundai Elantra N
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 WRX tS brings STI-like hardware upgrades including suspension tuning and Brembo brakes from the previous STI, but disappoints with no power increase from the 2.4L boxer engine. While it offers the closest thing to an STI experience available in the US market, the 271 hp output feels underwhelming when the engine has proven capable of 350+ hp with aftermarket tuning.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Subaru WRX tS: The new STI? Full review and track test.
pros: Adjustable suspension makes noticeable difference
Comfortable daily driver with track capability
All-wheel drive system provides confidence
Manual transmission preferred by 83% of buyers
Ricaro seats with good bolstering
Can handle various driving conditions
cons: Viscous coupler less advanced than STI system
expertReviews.verdict: The WRX tS is a capable performance sedan that bridges the gap until a proper STI returns. While it lacks the advanced drivetrain of the discontinued STI, the adjustable suspension and overall package make it a very competent daily driver that can handle track duty. Most drivers won't exceed its capabilities, though enthusiasts will miss the STI's more sophisticated all-wheel drive system.
